        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer356910990" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14094810760614917889">If someone wished to write an how NOT to, he /she should follow how this book reads. The is an book that reminds me that the President of the United State never let the word AIDS leave his mouth until a friend of his Rock Hudson died of it. No one wanted to do anything about it as long as it was kept within the blacks, queers, and hemophiliacs. As long as it was GRID it didn&apos;t matter.<br/>When they were told that it was bloodborne and there was a test for it, the American Red Cross didn&apos;t want to run</span>
  <span id="freeText14094810760614917889" style="display:none">If someone wished to write an how NOT to, he /she should follow how this book reads. The is an book that reminds me that the President of the United State never let the word AIDS leave his mouth until a friend of his Rock Hudson died of it. No one wanted to do anything about it as long as it was kept within the blacks, queers, and hemophiliacs. As long as it was GRID it didn't matter.<br />When they were told that it was bloodborne and there was a test for it, the American Red Cross didn't want to run the test because it cut into their profits. This is a great book and should be required reading before graduation.</span>
